snippet.textDisplay: When people get so excited talking about their traditions and celebrations or cooking with their family their excitement is infectious, and I feel like the only rational response to that is to also get excited and to ask if you could be a part of it. Tamales look so frickin delicious. My grandpa and his family left Russia and Germany in ww2 and when he came to Canada he was ashamed of his culture because of the atrocities that had been committed. When he was older he started to make more of the food he had growing up. He passed away when I was little, but we still have days where my family makes homemade pierogis, borscht, fish head soup, sauerkraut, cabbage rolls,  and sausages.
